---
description: Draft a repository rule proposal from the latest task
agent: rule-reviewer
subtask: true
---

Decide whether the latest task reveals a real standards gap.

Use the following evidence:

## Worktree status
!`git status --short`

## Unstaged diff
!`git diff -- .`

## Staged diff
!`git diff --cached -- .`

Read:
@standards/10_rule_proposal_template.md
@standards/09_review_prompt.md
@standards/11_changelog.md
@standards/04_python_rules_experimental.md
@standards/06_vue3_rules_experimental.md

Decision rules:
1. Propose a rule only if the pattern is realistically recurring.
2. Do not propose style-only rules that belong in formatter/lint tools.
3. Prefer experimental rules before stable rules unless the case is already repeatedly validated.
4. If no real standards gap exists, output exactly: no proposal.

If a proposal is justified, output using the structure from @standards/10_rule_proposal_template.md.
Also add a short recommendation at the end:
- recommended target: stable / experimental / reject
- reason: one sentence
